bilingual.target: 你看见那个漂亮宝贝了吗？

bilingual.source: This baby loves to listen to lullabies.

bilingual.source: This pretty baby has such a cute smile.
bilingual.target: 这个漂亮宝贝笑起来真可爱。
宝贝的笑声让所有人都开心。

bilingual.source: Her little daughter is such a pretty baby.

bilingual.source: He always calls his grandson a pretty baby.

bilingual.source: She bought a new toy for her pretty baby.
bilingual.target: 她给她的漂亮宝贝买了一个新玩具。

bilingual.source: They are preparing the room for the upcoming baby.
bilingual.target: 他们正在为即将出生的宝贝准备房间。

list.abstract: 《baby》是加拿大歌手贾斯汀·比伯演唱的英文流行歌曲，由贾斯汀·比伯、Tricky Stewart等共同作词谱曲，收录在专辑《My World 2.0》中，2010年1月18日发行，是《QQ飞车手游》游戏背景音乐。 贾斯汀·比伯凭借单曲《Baby》获得第27届MTV音乐奖最佳新人。《Baby》是贾斯汀·比伯的成名作，并在美国唱片业协会（RIAA）受到钻石认证，成为有史以来最畅销数字音乐之一。
baby是一个英语单词，名词、动词、形容词，作名词时意为“婴儿，婴孩；孩子气的人；（Baby）人名；（法、葡）巴比；（英）巴比，芭比（女名）；（俄）巴贝”，作动词时意为“纵容，娇纵；把……当婴儿般对待”，作形容词时意为“婴儿的；幼小的”。

yingyinNormal.en: It worked. Oh, baby, baby, baby. Oh, baby, baby, baby.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有效了，喔，宝贝，宝贝，宝贝 喔，宝贝，宝贝，宝贝

yingyinNormal.en: Do what you gotta do, baby.
yingyinNormal.zh: 去吧，宝贝

yingyinNormal.en: Baby girl, what did you do?
yingyinNormal.zh: 宝贝女儿，你干什么了？

yingyinNormal.en: With this baby we'll never be lost.
yingyinNormal.zh: 有了这个宝贝，我们永远不会迷路。

yingyinNormal.en: But then, later that night... Yeah, baby.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但那晚的晚些时候…好啊，宝贝。

yingyinNormal.en: You like it, baby? Oh, my God, it's beautiful.
yingyinNormal.zh: 宝贝，你喜欢吗？天呐，太美了。

yingyinNormal.en: That's an A! Let me smell that! That's real, baby!
yingyinNormal.zh: 是个A，让我闻一下，是真的，宝贝！

yingyinNormal.en: Come in. Hey baby, I'm back. Hey Ryan, what's up?
yingyinNormal.zh: 请进。宝贝，我回来了。莱恩，你好吗？

yingyinNormal.en: That's... That's was... Oh my God. That's Fergie baby.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那不是… 我的天。那是弗姬，宝贝。

yingyinNormal.en: Ooh, looks like I'm gonna have sex tonight. Hey, baby...
yingyinNormal.zh: 看起来我今晚要有"性"福了，宝贝...

yingyinNormal.en: Hello. I'm... Dory! Dory! You're here. Oh my baby!
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们好，我……多莉！多莉！你来了。我的宝贝！

yingyinNormal.en: My jersey's really messed up. Don't worry about that, baby.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我的毛线衣都弄脏了。别担心这个了，宝贝儿。

yingyinNormal.en: Come on,baby! Come on!
yingyinNormal.zh: 快啊，宝贝。

yingyinNormal.en: Have fun, baby girl.
yingyinNormal.zh: 玩的开心，宝贝女儿。

yingyinNormal.en: You're the bravest man I've ever known. I love you, baby. Not like "baby," like... because you look like a little weird baby-man.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你是我遇过最勇敢的人。我爱你，宝贝。不是说那个"宝宝"，是说宝贝。因为你看起来像一个奇怪的小宝宝。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm bugging out, baby. I need you to talk me down.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我彻底慌了，宝贝，你得让我冷静下来。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm so lucky to have you in my life, baby. Gloria.
yingyinNormal.zh: 生命中有你，我真的太幸运了，宝贝。歌洛莉亚。

yingyinNormal.en: Giving you my baby? You think I'd give you my child after this?
yingyinNormal.zh: 把我的宝贝给你们? 把孩子给两个骗子?

yingyinNormal.en: Baby, she doesn't have to. You're just supposed to turn them in.
yingyinNormal.zh: 宝贝，她不需要开口，你应该自觉交上去。

yingyinNormal.en: I have to, baby, daddy has to. Ice them. No, no, no!
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不得不这么做，宝贝，爸爸也无奈，做掉他们。不，不，不！

数据源自2016.6-2023.6年8年间全四级试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight>考纲释义</highlight>
精选实考、考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2016-2023年51套试卷，包括阅读、听力、翻译等所有题型。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2016-2023年8年间试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Park Yeon Soo conceived (构想) this city of the future back in 1986. He considers Songdo his <highlight>baby</highlight>. Park sees himself as a visionary.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 早在1986年，Park Yeon Soo 就构思了这座未来城市，他视松岛为自己的孩子，并认为自己是个预言家。

examination_example.sentence: The city is not empty. There are mothers pushing <highlight>baby</highlight> carriages, old women with walkers-even in the middle of the day, when it's 90 degrees out.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 新城并非空城。这里有推着婴儿车的母亲，有带着助行器的老妇人——即使是在中午，外面有90华氏度(约合20摄氏度)的时候也是如此。

examination_example.sentence: Their <highlight>babies</highlight> retain the ability to produce their own chlorophyll, though they can't generate energy from sunlight until they've eaten enough algae to steal the necessary genes, which they can't yet produce on their own.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 它们的后代延续了这种可以自己制造叶绿素的能力，尽管直到它们吃掉足够多的藻类以获取这种必要的基因(它们还无法自己制造这种基因)，它们才能够从阳光中制造能量。

examination_example.sentence: Thirty years after he imagined the city, Park's <highlight>baby</highlight> is close to 70 percent built, with 36, 000 people living in the business district and 90, 000 residents in greater Songdo.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在他构想出此城的30年后，他的“孩子”已经建成近70%，商业区居民有3.6万人，大松岛地区居民有9万人。

examination_example.sentence: According to the work of Professor James Vaupel and his co-researchers, 50% of <highlight>babies</highlight> born in the US in 2007 have a life expectancy of 104 or more.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据 James Vaupel 教授及其合作者的研究，2007年在美国出生的婴儿中，有50%的预期寿命为104岁，甚至更长。

examination_example.sentence: Broadly the same holds for the UK, Germany, France, Italy and Canada, and for Japan 50% of 2007 <highlight>babies</highlight> can expect to live to 107.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 英国、德国、法国、意大利和加拿大的情况大致相同，而在日本，2007年出生的婴儿中有50%的人预计能活到107岁。

examination_example.sentence: Like cats, <highlight>babies</highlight> appear to engage in what's called "preferential looking"— looking longer at things that are interesting or unusual than things they perceive as normal.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 和猫一样，婴儿似乎也会进行所谓的“优先寻找”，即比起它们认为正常的事物，它们看有趣或不寻常的事物的时间更长。

examination_example.sentence: Psychologists have shown that <highlight>babies</highlight> apparently expect their world to comply with the laws of physics and cause and effect as early as two months of age.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 心理学家表示，婴儿显然早在两个月大的时候就期望自己的世界符合物理学和因果律。

examination_example.sentence: Scientists have explored this idea with other endearing creatures: <highlight>babies</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 科学家们与其他可爱的生物-婴儿一起研究了这个想法。

examination_example.sentence: When <highlight>babies</highlight> expectations are violated in experiments like the ones performed with the cats, they react much like their animal friends.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当像在猫咪身上进行的实验一样，当违反婴儿的预期时，它们的反应就像动物朋友一样。

examination_example.sentence: Compared to 84 percent of <highlight>Baby</highlight> Boomers who've perhaps had the same home number for 50 years.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 相比之下，婴儿潮一代中有84%的人可能50年来一直拥有相同的住房号码。

examination_example.sentence: That said, to be honest the only people who ever ring our home phone are our <highlight>Baby</highlight> Boomers parents.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 也就是说，说实话，唯一给我们家打电话的人是我们婴儿潮一代的父母。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>baby</highlight> was born and update texts were setting out quickly from the overjoyed grandmother, Teresa.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 孩子出生了，欣喜若狂的奶奶特蕾莎很快发来了更新短信。

examination_example.sentence: After the <highlight>babies</highlight> finished eating  the keeper asked, “Would you like to help feed the adult squirrels, too?”
